If the play All My Sons accurately reflects American society, then many readers would conclude that our society is selfish, corrupt, and immoral. Explain whether you think this portrayal is accurate and fair today. Refer to at two scenes from the play as you examine the morality of American culture today.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I think that the American society today is very selfish. People will do almost anything to get ahead in the world or make sure there life is better. In All my Sons Kate is a good example of this. She is very selfish and she will never change to anyone else’s needs. Whenever someone asks her to do something, if she does not like it she will just change the subject or say I do not want to talk about it and walk off. She acts like this always when someone might mention that Larry is gone. I think Sue is also selfish to ask Ann to move away. She may not like how her husband acts around Chris but that is not Chris’s fault. For her to ask them to move away is very selfish. Keller is selfish as well by not telling Chris the truth about his business. If he really loved Chris and wanted Chris’s respect he would have told him the truth. American society is selfish in my opinion and it is always about them.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00CC00><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmrcliffordsenglishclasses.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wothes2>WotheS2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00CC00>(2/12/03 9:13:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmrcliffordsenglishclassesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  All My Sons</span><hr size=1> I think the play All My Sons has an accurate portrayal of the American society.  The people that live in our society are very selfish, corrupt, and immoral.  In All My Sons<br>
Joe Keller is a good example of a person who is corrupt and selfish.  Joe lied to the court saying that he had nothing to do with the shipping of the damaged cylinder heads, which is entirely untrue.  He is the one who told Herb to ship them out because he was afraid he would lose money.  He even admitted to lying about the whole incident.  He told Chris that he lied for his (Chris’s) sake and the future of the business.  He told Chris that if he told the truth to the court that he would have been put in jail and out of business because they needed the cylinder heads for the P-40’s.  Joe has kept this secret from Chris for many years because I think he feels bad for the decision he made.  I think that Joe is selfish because he seems to care more about the business rather than telling the truth and saving his friendship with Herb.  Another character who is very selfish is Sue.  I think it was very rude of her to ask Anne when she marries Chris if they could move away because Sue’s husband doesn’t like Chris.  I don’t think it is Ann’s problem that Dr. Bayliss doesn’t like Chris.  I don’t think that it is fair that Sue is asking Ann and Chris to move away when she and Jim could move away from the Chris.  Sue is selfish and doesn’t want to move because she does not want to lose what she has so she asks Ann if they could move away.  I think that there are many hundreds of people in this society who are like Joe and Sue very selfish and self-centered.  In my opinion the American society is very self, corrupt, and immoral.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCC99><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmrcliffordsenglishclasses.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hayley325>Hayley325</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00CC00>(2/12/03 9:48:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmrcliffordsenglishclassesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   All My Sons</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately, I think the play does in fact reflect the attitude of present day society. As seen in the play, Americans have the tendency to be more selfish than other cultures, which may even lead to corrupt and immoral thoughts and actions to produce a desired outcome. This is seen in certain scenes of All My Sons. An example of this is Joe’s justification of his horrible actions, stating that his son never flew p-40’s, and as a result was not completely unjust. Of course this does not justify anything, but since it did not affect him directly he is able to dismiss the highly immoral and illegal actions with ease.  Another scene that comes to mind which demonstrates a selfish and even corrupt society is the act of both Kate and Joe hiding the truth from family and friends  to protect their own skins. The low morality level shown here is reflective of today’s American society, and the ruthlessness that is possessed by many.  In the future, we as a society will hopefully raise the bar for all things concerning morality, as well as selfish and corrupt actions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00CC00><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmrcliffordsenglishclasses.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teruin2pac>TeruiN2pac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00CC00>(2/13/03 10:38:53 am)</font><br>